    "description": "<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Turn-Based Tactical Warfare</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>WarForwards</strong> is a turn-based strategy game centered on tactical combat and careful planning. Battles take place on grid-based maps where positioning, timing, and unit management determine victory.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The game emphasizes deliberate decision-making over fast reflexes, rewarding players who enjoy thinking several moves ahead.</p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Tactical Combat and Unit Management</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Each encounter challenges players to deploy and maneuver units efficiently while responding to enemy actions. Success depends on understanding unit strengths, terrain advantages, and turn order rather than overwhelming force.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >WarForwards is designed for fans of <strong>classic tactical war games</strong> who prefer structured, rule-driven combat.</p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >A Focused Strategy Experience</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The presentation is clean and functional, keeping attention on the battlefield and tactical choices. There are no distractions from progression systems or narrative layers — the focus remains squarely on strategy and combat.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >This is a <strong>single-player tactical strategy experience</strong> aimed at players who value planning, structure, and replayability.</p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >Key Features</h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Turn-based tactical combat</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Grid-based battlefield design</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Strategic unit positioning and planning</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Classic war-game–inspired mechanics</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Replayable encounters focused on mastery</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Single-player strategy experience</p></li></ul>",
